items.name: Cucouroux (Granblue Fantasy) - ククル | LyCORIS - LoHa
items.description:
Cucouroux (Granblue Fantasy)

The model was carefully created to avoid overfitting at a resolution of 1024.

Training is done with batch size=8, gradient accumulation step=16.

It should probably work on many models.

It seems to be available for realistic models such as chilloutmix.

We recommend using a weight of 0.8 to 1.0.

LyCORIS (LoHa), please install and use a1111-sd-webui-locon.

Usage

Match file_name with the name of the LoHa file you downloaded.

basic example:

<lora:file_name:1>best illustration, 2D, BREAK
cucouroux, thst, 1girl, solo, blue eyes, low twintails, blonde hair, medium breasts,  (white) beret, green ribbon, blue ribbon, belt, detached sleeves, white skirt, collarbone, bare shoulders, white jacket

basic example (nude):

<lora:file_name:1>best illustration, 2D, BREAK
cucouroux, thst, 1girl, solo, blue eyes, low twintails, blonde hair, medium breasts,  completely nude,

Negative prompt:

(bar censor, censored), (mutant hand, mutant fingers:1.2) (worst quality, low quality:1.4), (lip, nose, tooth, rouge, lipstick, eyeshadow:1.4), (jpeg artifacts:1.4), (abs, muscular, rib:1.0), greyscale, monochrome, dusty sunbeams, trembling, motion lines, motion blur, emphasis lines, text, title, logo, signature,(simple background:1.2)

I like her very much among the characters in Granblue Fantasy.

I would like to see it added to Granblue Fantasy Versus: Rising!

For this to happen, her appeal needs to be more widespread.

I look forward to seeing lots of art created by all of you.

items.name: Moth Girls [Lycoris]
items.description:
This model is designed to generate moth girls of all shapes and sizes. It was trained a large number of them so you can get all kinds of styles with various optional features, but it may be a bit overtrained. I would highly recommend using this at weights of 0.8-0.6 depending on what you're going for.

Prompts that can help specific features:
Antennae - antennae, moth antennae, feather antennae

Neck fuzz - neck fur, fur collar

Wings - moth wings, multiple wings

Arms - 4/four arms, multiple arms, multiple limbs, fuzzy arms

Model used was Kenshi.


Special quirks:
-Sometimes it can decide that wings are actually supposed to be coats. If it does, put ((fur coat)) in the negative prompt and it should correct itself.

-Sometimes they really like to have their arms spread or their hands clasped in front of them. Try putting "arms spread" or "hands clasped" or something like that in the negative if they won't stop (or just use ControlNet).

(The Gardevoir girl who shows up in all my gens is an OC of mine named Sonia. She's basically my mascot at this point. She uses thesauceer's Gardevoir Lora)

items.name: Sentinel Diffusion
items.description:
Sentinel Diffusion v1.0

The model is mainly designed to output art with vivid colors, fine details, and a realistic touch, free from the heavy anime bias commonly found in some existing models (but still capable of generating good anime style art).

One of the primary objectives of the model was to allow for the generation of impressive outputs with simple prompts while also providing the flexibility to create specific and complex results with the right prompt engineering.

The model can generate a diverse range of content, including

  • Consistent characters

  • Realism

  • Striking landscapes

  • Abstract art

  • Fantasy

  • Sci-Fi

  • And more!

items.name: Row of 35 people POSE , multi view，35个人的动作PNG图，多视图
items.description:
没有什么，就是一排人物的动作骨骼图而已。

安装CONTRONET，点启动CONTRONET，预处理器选 无，处理模型选OPENPOSE，把这个骨架图拖进去就好。不用什么提示词，可以搭配各种大模型（前提是大模型里有人）。

35人版本：应该是现在8G显存显卡的pose人数极限了。分辨率最好是1824X1568(8G显存)。快速采样方法:用DPM++ 2M的7步(7Steps)或者用DPM++ SDE Karras的5步(5Steps)。

12人版本：应该是现在单排的人数极限了。分辨率最好是2048X352，要开面部修复。显卡好的开高清修复(8G显存不够)，快速采样方法:Euler a的7步(7Steps)或者DPM++ SDE Karras的5步(5Steps)

优点是能显示更多人物，背景变好了。缺点就是分辨率低了，脸变形严重。

8人版本：分辨率最好是2048X512，要开面部修复。显卡好的开高清修复(8G显存不够)。

5人版本：使用16:9 图片比例更好 ，1920X1080或 768X432分辨率（开高清修复，低分辨率会有更多样的角色）

关于采样方法(Sampler)的对比：

快组：Euler a、Euler、LMS、DPM++ 2M、DPM fast、LMS Karras、DPM++ 2M Karras 这些都是一个速度，比较快但是模糊

慢组：Heun、DPM2、DPM2 a、DPM++ 2S a、DPM++ SDE、DPM2 Karras、DPM2 a Karras、DPM++ 2S a Karras、DPM++ SDE Karras、DDIM、PLMS

这些都是一个速度，慢几乎一半，但是清楚一些所以可以少几乎一半的采样迭代步数(Steps)，综合下来也差不多。但是，根据分辨率高低不同，在低步数下有不同的表现。

这个动作POSE图用于测试各种模型，一张顶很多张~包括正面、背面、侧面、跪势、坐势、曲腿

35个人的视图。为了微调每个人不同的动作，我渲染了接近1千次。不过不同的模型角度是不同的，出错的就说明这个模型里面没有那个角度。

just POSES PNG.

Install CONTRONET, "ENABLE". select "None" for the preprocessor, select "OPENPOSE" for the model, and drag the PNG into it. GENERATE!

Without any prompting words, it can match various models

To fine-tune the different movements of each person, I rendered close to 1,000 times

Sampler for fast rendering: DPM++ 2M (8Steps) or DPM++ SDE Karras (4Steps)

Test various models, one top several~including front, back, side, kneeling, sitting, and bent legs

View of 12 people. If there are many errors, does it mean that the diversity of the model is insufficient?

35 person version: It should be the limit for the number of poses on 8G graphics cards. The resolution is preferably 1824X1568.Sampler for fast rendering: DPM++ 2M (8Steps) or DPM++ SDE Karras (4Steps)

12-person version: resolution 2048X352.Due to the reduced resolution, the background of the screen is much better, and the diversity of characters is also increased.Sampler for fast rendering: Euler a(7Steps) or DPM++ SDE Karras(5Steps)

8-person version: resolution 2048X512. open a 'Restore faces'.If the graphics card is properly opened 'Hires. fix'. The advantage is that it can display more characters. The disadvantage is that the resolution is low and the face is severely deformed

5-person version: uses a 16:9 image ratio that is better, with 1920 x 1080 or 768 x 432 resolution (with HD repair enabled, there will be more diverse characters at low resolutions)

View of 35 people. To fine tune the different movements of each person, I rendered close to 1,000 times. However, the angle is different for different models, and an error means that the model does not have that angle inside.

Shun:

This lora is capable of producing both versions of Sunohara Shun, from Blue Archive.

There is some tag overlap, so make sure to include the "activation token" so that the outfit steers in the right direction.

There are some tags that are common to both forms, tags for each and the common tags will be below.

The halo is inconsistent, but it generally gets the shape correct. It pretty much can't get the smaller details in the halo correct, but that is more or less a dataset issue.

Shun big has some bleed of the dress, but can generally be resolved if you use the tag halter dress instead of black dress.

Generally, the details will be consistent enough that you can get a good gen every 2 or 3 gens. All examples in this are gens from trying only a few times to get a somewhat decent halo.

The dataset was a bit annoying to work with on this one, as the artists didn't play nice with the halo, and the little bead thing that Shun big has.

I do think I want to try and train this again with a slightly more up to date dataset, as well as a higher resolution, because I think that is the biggest reason why the halo doesn't have all of the correct details.

not all of these tags are strictly required, but you will have to use most of them.

black hair, long hair, bangs, tiger ears, tiger girl, halo, green eyes

shun \(blue archive\), ponytail, large breasts, halter dress, chinese clothes, hair ornament, bridal gauntlets

items.name: Western Indo Fusion Saree
items.description:
If you'd like to support me and do more:
https://ko-fi.com/edgonkofi - commissions open!
If you're looking for a >>LoRA Making Tutorial<<

Western Indo Fusion Saree

We are back today in the world of Fusion Design for the purpose of reinventing and modernizing the Indian Saree with is a staple of South-Indian fashion, and a well renown piece of fashion throughout the globe!

In fact Saree is so popular that it is quite hard to make a LoRA that beats native SD at generating traditional saree.

Therefore, I have decided to take the route of fusion design to find a blind spot and make something that the AI is incapable of making without this LoRA.

Based on my experiments, I can assure you that it is unlikely that the AI can pull off this type of Western Indo Fusion Design!

Please tell me what you think of this new model in the review and comments section!

Get this LoRA and start designing

items.name: Haven Troopers - Metal Gear Solid
items.description:
The Haven Troopers! Also known as the FROGS or Frog Soldiers from Metal Gear Solid 4.

This is a lora trained on 52 hand picked images of Haven Troopers from MGS4. It was trained mostly on digital art, but there are some 3d renders in there for variety. It was trained on danbooru-style tags, so use those when trying to prompt - I've included the tags in a .txt file in the "Training Images" download below.

It works pretty well with most .ckpts, but I recommend Anything 4.5, I used it for all of the example images.

NOTES:

-You can remove the helmet by putting 'helmet' in negative prompts and prompting relevant facial tags

-It seems to understand the bodysuit, leg straps, and chest harness well, but the weird gasmask-helmet thing is probably the most inconsistent part of this lora.

-A number of images trained had the character holding guns, but depending on your model, it still probably can't do it very well.

Example prompt: (See example images, all images should still have their metadata. Just drag the images onto the PNG info tab and import it.)

Liquid Ocelot had good taste...

items.name: SDArt : Catstravaganza
items.description:
Model presentation

This is a model related to the "Picture of the Week" contest on Stable Diffusion discord.

You can find this dataset in a more complete model, SDArt : Complete Edition.

This present version is trained on dedicated tokens per user, and doesn't work like you may be used to.

I try to make a model out of all the submissions, for people to continue enjoy the theme after the event, and see a little of their designs in other people's creations. The token stays "SDArt" and I balance the learning on the low side, so that it doesn't just replicate creations.

The pictures were tagged using the token "SDArt", and an arbitrary token given to the user that submitted it.

The dataset is available below and is composed of 61 pictures.

This week's theme

Orb-like eyes, mischief, and surprise Cat paws tip-a-tap at your side With their fanged teeth and coy mystique They gaze up at you ever so sweet Won’t you give them a treat?

This POW’s all about our favorite feline friends wherein we are absolutely not biased. Be as creative as you can!

Whether it be a cat made of cotton candy, a grumpy cat made of storm clouds, or just your regular degular tabby cat. Bring them all here and may the best cat reign supreme!

“It’s raining cats and cats out here!”

  • Join us for a cat-stravaganza of fun

  • Cute and cuddly - show us your paw-sitively purrfect creations!

  • Whisk-er away your doubts and unleash your cat-titude

  • Wander into the canvas alongside your meow-gnificant feline friends!
